########## SUMMERY READ ONLY BELOW 4 LINES  #####################################################################################################################################################
LANGUAGE           ==  FILE TO CHECK                  = FROM dockerimage
 
JavaScript                      ==  ALL HAVE package.json mostly   =     node:20-alpine for all js app building
HTML/CSS/JS basics (Static Web) == index.html (script/style tags)  =     nginx:alpine
python                          == app.py / requirements.txt       =     python:3.11-slim       

##################################################################################################################################################################################################
# DevOps engineers typically use for frontend

1)  JavaScript types =1) Node.js, 2) React js,3) Vue,4) Angular js 5)next js
Node.js:    package.json (shows "express" or "node" deps)
React:      package.json (shows "react" + "react-dom")
Vue:        package.json (shows "vue")                     OR src/main.js (has Vue.createApp)
Angular:    package.json (shows "@angular/core")           OR angular.json (tells Angular) 
Next.js:    package.json (shows "next")                    OR next.config.js 
â€‹
# Docker base images (most used):

Node.js: node:20-alpine
React: node:20-alpine
Vue: node:20-alpine
Angular: node:20-alpine
Next.js: node:20-alpine


2) Other options: HTML/CSS/JS basics  =
HTML/CSS/JS basics: index.html (script/style tags)
:nginx:alpine

3) sometimes Python (Streamlit/Dash for quick ML dashboards).
Python Streamlit: app.py (import streamlit as st)
: python:3.11-slim
Python Dash: app.py (import dash)
: python:3.11-slim

--python:3.11-slim is often better than alpine for Python because 
many Python libraries (like pandas or numpy) are difficult to compile on Alpine but work instantly on slim (Debian-based).                


